markets.title: Will US average new COVID-19 cases ever **fall below March 2020 levels** in 2022?
markets.subtitle: <11,790 average new cases per day
markets.rules_primary: If the seven-day moving average of new COVID-19 cases for the United States according to the CDC is below 11,790 for a single day between Issuance and December 31, 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary:
Note that this Contract may close and expire early. It will expire the first 10:00 AM following the CDC reporting the event has occurred, the first 10:00 AM following data being released for December 31, 2022, or 10:00 AM on January 05, 2023.

Please note: In the event that the CDC is no longer publishing daily case totals at the Expiration Time, the seven-day average shall be calculated by dividing the CDC-published weekly case totals by 7.
